102	\section{Use in the project}
103	
104	The Picard group $\Pic(X)$ is the underlying \emph{set} (modulo isomorphism) of the Picard \emph{scheme} $\Pic_{C/k}$ in the curve case; the scheme structure adds a $k$-scheme of finite type representing the relative Picard functor $S \mapsto \Pic(C \times_k S) / \Pic(S)$.
105	
106	This chapter is therefore the gateway to:
107	\begin{itemize}
108	  \item Definition~\ref{def:Pic_functor} (Picard functor of $C/k$) --- quotient by $\Pic(S)$ uses Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_Pic_pullback}.
109	  \item Theorem~\ref{thm:Pic_representable} (representability of the Picard scheme) --- uses the full $\Pic$ machinery built here.
110	  \item Definition~\ref{def:ofCurve} (Abel--Jacobi map) --- defined via the line bundle $\mathcal O_{C \times C}(\Delta - p_1^* P)$ on $C \times C$, an explicit element of $\Pic(C \times C)$.
111	\end{itemize}
112	
113	Post-C1, all of these downstream consumers transitively depend on $\mathrm{instIsMonoidal\_W}$ via the $\mathrm{CommGroup}$ instance on $\Pic(X)$ (load-bearing for $\mathrm{LineBundle}$, $\Pic$, $\mathrm{Pic.pullback}$, $\mathrm{PicardFunctor}$, $\mathrm{PicardFunctorAb}$, and the Jacobian framework); the $\mathrm{Pic.pullback}$ arc additionally depends on Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj}. Both dependencies surface in \texttt{lean\_verify}'s axiom chain.
114	
115	\section{Mathlib gap}
116	
117	Mathlib has:
118	\begin{itemize}
119	  \item The abelian category of sheaves of $\mathcal O_X$-modules on a scheme $X$, together with the (presheaf-side) symmetric monoidal structure and the sheafification machinery.
120	  \item Quasi-coherence as data on a sheaf of modules.
121	  \item The skeleton-of-a-monoidal-category construction $\mathrm{Skeleton}\,C$ and the chain $\mathrm{BraidedCategory}\,C \Longrightarrow \mathrm{CommMonoid}\,(\mathrm{Skeleton}\,C) \Longrightarrow \mathrm{CommGroup}\,(\mathrm{Skeleton}\,C)^{\!\times}$ (\texttt{Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.Skeleton}).
122	  \item The ring-side precedent $\mathrm{CommRing.Pic}\,R = \mathrm{Shrink}\,(\mathrm{Skeleton}\,(\mathrm{SemimoduleCat}\,R))^{\!\times}$ (\texttt{Mathlib.RingTheory.PicardGroup:407}).
123	  \item The categorical pull-back functor $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f$ on quasi-coherent $\mathcal O$-modules (\texttt{Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Modules.Sheaf}).
124	\end{itemize}
125	
126	What is missing and supplied by this chapter:
127	\begin{itemize}
128	  \item The scheme-side $\mathrm{CommGroup}\,(\mathrm{LineBundle}\,X)$ instance, threading the skeleton-units idiom through $X.\mathrm{Modules}$. Transitively load-bearing on $\mathrm{instIsMonoidal\_W}$ (Chapter~\ref{chap:Modules_Monoidal}) for the required $\mathrm{BraidedCategory}\,(X.\mathrm{Modules})$.
129	  \item A scheme-morphism-functorial pull-back homomorphism $\Pic(Y) \to \Pic(X)$, currently sorry-bodied (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_Pic_pullback}).
130	  \item The monoidality iso $f^*(M \otimes N) \cong f^* M \otimes f^* N$ for the categorical pull-back on $\mathcal O$-modules, recorded as the named-deferred Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj}. Mathlib b80f227 has the analogous monoidality on the presheaf-side pushforward (\texttt{PresheafOfModules.PushforwardZeroMonoidal}) but no $\mathrm{Functor.Monoidal}$ instance for the pull-back of sheaves of modules.
131	\end{itemize}
132	
133	These are mapped to Phase~B/C step~1 of the project strategy. See also the cross-referenced load-bearing-disclosure paragraph in Chapter~\ref{chap:Modules_Monoidal} on $\mathrm{instIsMonoidal\_W}$.
